flightsim.simconnect.recv
Class RecvFacilitiesList

java.lang.Object
  flightsim.simconnect.recv.RecvPacket
      flightsim.simconnect.recv.RecvFacilitiesList
Direct Known Subclasses:
RecvAirportList, RecvNDBList, RecvVORList, RecvWaypointList
public abstract class RecvFacilitiesList
extends RecvPacket

The RecvFacilitiesList structure is used to provide information on the number of elements in a list of facilities returned to the client, and the number of packets that were used to transmit the data.

getArraySize

public int getArraySize()
Double word containing the number of elements in the list that are within this packet. For example, if there are 25 airports returned in the RecvAirportList structure, then this field will contain 25, but if there are 400 airports in the list and the data is returned in two packets, then this value will contain the number of entries within each packet.

Returns:
number of elements

getEntryNumber

public int getEntryNumber()
Double word containing the index number of this list packet. This number will be from 0 to getOutOf() - 1.

Returns:
